# {{ project_name }}

A [dropmcp](https://github.com/agoda-com/dropmcp) skills & prompts MCP server.

## Layout

```
skills/          # SKILL.md folders → MCP tools
prompts/         # PROMPT.md folders → MCP prompts
INSTRUCTIONS.md  # Server instructions ({% raw %}{{INSTRUCTION_SUMMARIES}}{% endraw %} placeholders)
server.py        # One-liner entrypoint
requirements.txt # Pinned dropmcp dependency
```

## Local development

Install dependencies (pins `dropmcp=={{ dropmcp_version }}`):

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Validate content:

```bash
python -c "import sys; from dropmcp.validate import run_validation; sys.exit(run_validation('skills', 'prompts'))"
```

Run the server (streamable-HTTP, catalog UI at `/`, MCP endpoint at `/mcp`):

```bash
DROPMCP_PORT=8080 python server.py
```

## Docker

```bash
docker build -t {{ project_slug }} .
docker run --rm -p 8080:8080 {{ project_slug }}
```

Open http://localhost:8080/ to browse skills and prompts.

{% if include_promptfoo_evals %}
## Skill evaluations (Promptfoo)

Eval configs live under `tests/`. Run them locally (requires an OpenAI API key):

```bash
cd tests
npx promptfoo@latest eval
npx promptfoo@latest view
```

CI runs `promptfoo eval` when `OPENAI_API_KEY` is configured as a repository secret.
{% endif %}

## Adding content

1. **Skill** — create `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` with YAML frontmatter (`name`, `category`, `description`, optional `instruction_summary`). Add supporting files alongside for `skill://` resource links.
2. **Prompt** — create `prompts/<name>/PROMPT.md` with frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `arguments`). Use `{% raw %}{{arg}}{% endraw %}` placeholders in the body.

Re-run the validation command above after changes.
